<br>
As for a **specific** Class Defining Raid role ... the only thing that has crossed my mind over and over would be some sort of Anti-Summoning Spell. This spell would NOT be cast on the MOB rather on a player. That way we can keep the Enchanter alive when he/she tashes or the Shaman alive when he/she slows.<br>
<br>
The spell would not pull aggro from the Main Tank because it would be cast on a PLAYER not a MOB. It would have to be very short term, something along the lines of 10 to 12 seconds and have a recast time of 1 minute. That way a Raid would need 2 to 3 Druids at a raid to keep your 'chanter, Shammy and/or Cleric alive because we could not cast this &quot;buff&quot; on more then one target per MOB encounter. Or the recast time could be as low as the duration of the buff ( ie 10 to 12 seconds ) but that would allow someone to be completely immune to summon for the whole fight because we could chain cast it.<br>
<br>
Of course, just because the MOB can not summon the 'chanter/shaman/cleric does not mean that they would be completely safe. The MOB could always just run after them, but at least if done right, the 'chanter/shaman/cleric might have enough room to back away and hope the Tanks can regain aggro before he/she gets pummeled to death once the MOB reaches them.<br>
<br>
Another way a MOB could reach out and touch someone who has an anti-summon buff on would be a well placed AoE spell in the direction of the 'chanter/shaman/cleric which of course would put our little caster huddle in the corner at risk. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So, maybe it is just me, but the ONLY real beneficial &quot;Class Defining&quot; raid ability left that is not already in the game would be a spell along this line. Also, it does not seem like it would be overpowered or make encounters trivial for the reasons I listed. /shrug<br>
<br>
Oh, and VI before you go ahead and put my idea in the game ( or &quot;our&quot; Idea, in case others too have thought about this and posted the idea before me ), <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  lemme make sure you know that making it drop ONLY off of Emperor Ssraeshza in the Ssraeshza Temple would not be funny <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Lemme suggest Juggs or something along those lines. Putting spells in the game that are all but impossible to attain except for the server's Uber Guilds is not my idea of class balancing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
